Squizzy::

her old proccessor still had energy running through it.  It had a 
small battery on it as a temorary back up power source.  it still 
tried to function, but wasn't finding it's proper connections. 

Squizzy lay there, not moving, in stasis lock.


--- In nbwrpg@egroups.com, Yanshosh@a... wrote:
> ::Zardus::
> 
> Zardus looks up from Squizzy as Cybershark comes in. "Ah, yes.." he 
says in 
> reply to the bot's request, "I may have a mission for you. But 
first, go into 
> one of the CR chambers. You have been in the Cybertronian Fire, and 
have some 
> info that I might need. The CR chamber will automatically download 
it, and 
> then I'll give you the mission."
> 
> He glances back at the other console, with Squizzy's old main 
proccessor, to 
> see if it had gotten anywhere yet.
